The Catholic Bishop of Sokoto Diocese, Bishop Matthew Hassan Kukah within the week donated bags of rice to Persons Living with Disabilities (PLWD) and other religious organization in the state as part of his assistance to the Ramadan fast. Bishop Kukah before presenting the donations urged beneficiaries to ensure that they use this Holy months of Muslims in seeking the face of God for His intervention in the global pandemic. Represented by Rev. Father Lawrence Emehel, the Bishop admonished beneficiaries to see the annual gesture from the Sokoto Catholic Diocese as a true demonstration of brotherhood and show of love. Rev Father Emehel who was accompanied by Rev Father Chris Omotosho, Rev Sister Ann and a member of Christian Women Organisaron appealed to them to always ensure that they adhere strictly to advise by health expert in respect of the ravaging COVID 19. Kukah who said the grains was given to support the group members’ in supplementing their feedings during this Ramadan season, further urged them to pray for unity and progress of Nigeria and Nigerians. “I implore all of you to observe regular hand washing, use of face masks, using hand sanitizers ensure self-distancing and other measures set out by the WHO. The benefiting groups were represented by their leaders, Malam Dahiru Ayuba of (PLWD) and Malam Umar Suleiman of Da’awat Sunnah and Followers of Prophetic Traditions at the presentation. Unanimously, the groups commended Bishop Kukah and Christians in the state for their consistent show of love and brotherhood at all tines. 